Setting up Python 3.12 and pythonnet

1. Verify Python 3.12 is installed:
   Run the following command to check the Python version:
   python3.12 --version
   Ensure it returns Python 3.12.x.

2. Install pythonnet:
   Use pip to install the latest version of pythonnet:
   python3.12 -m pip install --upgrade pythonnet

3. Verify Mono is installed and up-to-date:
   Ensure you have Mono version 6.12 or higher:
   mono --version
   If Mono is outdated, download and install the latest version from:
   https://www.mono-project.com/download/stable/

4. Run the script:
   Use Python 3.12 to execute the script:
   python3.12 r3_writer.py

Installation of Python 3.10 and setup for `pythonnet`

1. Download Python 3.10:
   - Go to https://www.python.org/downloads/release/python-31012/ and download the source code for Python 3.10.
   - Extract the downloaded file:
     tar -xvf Python-3.10.12.tgz
     cd Python-3.10.12

2. Install OpenSSL:
   - Download the latest version from https://www.openssl.org/source/
   - Extract, compile, and install OpenSSL:
     tar -xvf openssl-3.4.0.tar.gz
     cd openssl-3.4.0
     ./config
     make
     sudo make install

3. Configure and compile Python with OpenSSL:
   - Clean previous configurations:
     make clean
   - Configure Python to use OpenSSL:
     ./configure --with-openssl=/usr/local/ssl --enable-shared
   - Compile and install Python:
     make -j$(sysctl -n hw.ncpu)
     sudo make altinstall

4. Verify Python and OpenSSL:
   - Open Python 3.10 and verify:
     python3.10
     Inside the interpreter, run:
     import ssl
     print(ssl.OPENSSL_VERSION)

5. Install `pythonnet`:
   - Use pip to install:
     python3.10 -m pip install pythonnet

6. Update Mono:
   - Go to https://www.mono-project.com/download/stable/ and download the latest version.
   - Install the `.pkg` file and verify:
     mono --version

7. Run your script:
   - Run your script using Python 3.10:
     python3.10 r3_writer.py


